<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5390.1.1>
    dc:creator "Bertani, Rogério" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Taxonomic revision and cladistic analysis of Lasiodora C. L. Koch, 1850 (Araneae, Theraphosidae) with notes on related genera" ;
    bibo:endPage "116" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-12-27" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "5390" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434522>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434524>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434662>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434664>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434666>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434672> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434522>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8–15. Stridulatory setae of prolateral coxa I, males. 8, L. parahybana, Brazil, state of Pernambuco, Cabo de Santo Agostinho. 9, L. sertaneja n. sp. (IBSP 4127B). 10, L. camurujipe n. sp. (MNRJ 7764). 11, L. franciscana n. sp. (IBSP 8050). 12, L. subcanens (IBSP 9546). 13, L. klugi (MNRJ 7742). 14, L. benedeni (IBSP 84328). 15, L. klugi, Brazil, state of Bahia, Ilhéus. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434522/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434524>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Strict consensus of three cladograms obtained with setk.run and concavity 7.8125. All characters non-additive. Fit = 7.38251, length = 161.30. Absolute/relative Bremer support are in each node. The names of the genera and species in the cladogram are in accordance with the results obtained in the cladistic analysis carried out here, and do not consider the new genera and transfers proposed by Galleti-Lima et al. 2023." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434524/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434662>
    dc:description "FIGURES 255─260. Lasiodora franciscana n. sp. (255─259) male holotype (IBSP 8622). (255─257) left palp bulb. 255, retrolateral. 256, prolateral. 257, dorsal. (258─259) left tibial apophysis. 258, ventral. 259, prolateral. 260, female paratype (IBSP 4865C), spermathecae, dorsal. Scale bar = 1mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434662/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434664>
    dc:description "FIGURES 261─265. Lasiodora franciscana n. sp., male holotype (IBSP 8622), stridulatory apparatus. (261─262) left maxilla, retrolateral. 261, general view. 262, detail of spiniform setae on upper area. (263─265) left coxa I, prolateral. 263, general view. 264, detail of stridulatory setae. 265, detail of area below suture. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434664/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434666>
    dc:description "FIGURES 266─270. Lasiodora franciscana n. sp., female paratype (IBSP 4865C), stridulatory apparatus. (266─267) left maxilla, retrolateral. 266, general view. 267, detail of spiniform setae on upper area. (268─270) left coxa I, prolateral. 268, general view. 269, detail of stridulatory setae. 270, detail of area below suture. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434666/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10434672>
    dc:description "FIGURES 283─284. Maps showing records of Lasiodora franciscana n. sp. in Northestern, Southeastern and Central-west Brazil. 283, relief. 284, biomes. Forested areas of Fig. 284 are in green shades, on east (Brazilian Atlantic Forest) and on west (Amazon). Brown areas are of Cerrado; and pinkish, Caatinga. “?” represents questionable record." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10434672/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

